===2020 census===

As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Lowell had a population of 70. The [[population density]] was 70.1 inhabitants per square mile (27.1/km<sup>2</sup>). The median age was 53.0 years. 27.1% of residents were under the age of 18 and 27.1% of residents were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females there were 112.1 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 96.2 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A46965&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A46965&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A46965&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

There were 30 households in Lowell, of which 26.7% had children under the age of 18 living in them. Of all households, 56.7% were married-couple households, 0.0% were cohabitating couples, 30.0% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 13.3% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. 40.0% of households were non-families; 40.0% of all households were made up of individuals; and 26.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 33 housing units at an average density of 33.1 per square mile (12.8/km<sup>2</sup>), of which 9.1% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 100.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL"/>

The age distribution was 30.0% under the age of 20, 1.4% from 20 to 24, 10.0% from 25 to 44, 31.4% from 45 to 64, and 27.1% age 65 or older. The gender makeup was 52.9% male and 47.1% female.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

